    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how the <strong>Ibhayi Pharmacy Prescription Management System</strong> collects, uses, stores, and protects your personal and health-related information. By using our system, you agree to the practices outlined below.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Such as your name, ID number, email address, phone number, and account login details.</li>
        <li><strong>Health Information:</strong> Including prescription details, known allergies, doctor information, and medication history.</li>
        <li><strong>System Usage Data:</strong> Such as login history, pages accessed, and other usage patterns to ensure system integrity and security.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Information is collected and used to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Manage user accounts and authenticate access securely.</li>
        <li>Enable pharmacists to dispense prescriptions accurately and safely.</li>
        <li>Notify customers when prescriptions are ready for collection.</li>
        <li>Generate reports for regulatory compliance and patient records.</li>
        <li>Improve system functionality and user experience.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        We implement industry-standard encryption and security protocols to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Passwords are securely stored using encryption, and sensitive information is restricted to authorized personnel only.
    </p>

    <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell or trade personal data. Information may be shared only in the following cases:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>With your consent, for healthcare purposes.</li>
        <li>With healthcare professionals (e.g., your doctor or pharmacist) involved in your care.</li>
        <li>To comply with applicable laws or valid legal processes.</li>
        <li>As part of an emergency situation to protect your life or health.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
        You have the right to view, correct, or delete your personal data stored in our system. You may also request information on how your data has been used. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below.
    </p>

